rComments: Bob Logan, in short he likes to be called Bob. He is a very good prof, it is very easy to underestimate him. His level of grading depends on you. If you clearly understand his concepts and are capable of relating such you will do good. You will excel if you take advantage of office hours, he is encouraging and wants his students to succeed,

He didn't give any feedback for papers, and he deliberately gave us a lower mark on the first assignment, only to amend it on the second.  However, he gave me a generous extension when I had no idea how I would have finished my other assignments in time. Additionally, his interdisciplinary approach to scientific content is admirable.
physics of poetry seminar. watch out girls. i'm about to file a sexual harassment complaint.
Hey with what velocity would a meteorite have to hit the physics building to to wipe out physics for good? (Let's assume g=9.8m/s/s)

-Poor commnication skills... he spends all class attempting to prove something and after an hour ends up where he started... I found my solutions were more clear than his... My advise for him is to check out Prof Walter Lewin on youtube and try to copy his style
Worst prof!!! It took me a long time to like physics again after him

One of the worst profs I have ever had. He always arrived late, took for granted things that we "should" have known, and  very poorly explained concepts and theories. He always made a point of saying that we had a textbook, and to learn from it without ever offering further examples to reinforce any hard to understand ideas. A waste of my money.
Logan was a unique prof.  I thought he a charming person that loved to enjoy himself.  Could have taught more clearly, but the course wasn;t very difficult.
Horrible prof, don't know what he is talking about

there are times when you dont understand what hes talking about because he likes to use his own variables. Read ahead. his examples sometimes help. he can be funny. Theres no point in going to wednesday classes with him because all he does is take up hmwk, unless you havent done it. The test was easy, enough mistakes found to boost up your mark.
Very unclear.  The tutorials were so much more useful.

Logan is quite a bad lecturer. He doesn't explain many things, just writes equations down, and when he does explain things you're too bored to pay attention. Plus he seems **** sometimes. But upside, tests and exam were EASY.

BORING BORING BORING LECTURES! I'm not sure if he actually knows what he is teaching. All he teaches from the lecture are EXACTLY the same as the textbook but the exams were WAYYYYY harder. Exams were all multiple choices....it may seem easier, but it has no part mark. AND ITS HARD!
he is very nice, smart, and funny.. he has it all in his head but i guess he just can't say it out loud.
can the man get more confusing? nice guy, very smart, understands the material and likes to derive stuff, approachable but does not know how to teach 1st year physics students.... read the book...

His lectures are very BORING.  You don't even have to go because there are only two essay for his part of the year, and they don't have to cover what is lectured.  Too bad he's retiring after this year.

Yhis is a joint course for artsies and I think prof. Logan has really hit his stride.  His books are fascinating!  This course is fun, imaginative, and really easy to keep on top of.  If you're looking to pick up an easy science mark, this is it!
Very confusing lectures, d/t made up variables that he interchanged at will and endless derivations of formulas.  Exams/test were fair and he was very approachable.

OMG TAKE THIS SEMINAR!!!!  Very boring but you never have to go!  No tests/exams/participation marks.  You will never have to recall anything learned in class.  3 independent research essays.  Easiest A ever.

I for one think he's wonderful...great tests, explains things, tells physics as a story...it's my favourite class
nice guy but alwasys derive derive derive....1 pg 2 pg 3 pg..."oh, you're not responsible for this and this and this on the test"  Teach us something we need!
so boring....pure deriving....pure formulas....
T(up), T(down), N, calculus, derivatives..what? am i in phy110?

My lordie...can that man get anymore confusing?! He just goes on and makes his own VARIABLES. I wish he would use universal math symbols! Phy138 learns the same thing, and that prof is a better teacher. We're BASIC PHYSICS not PHY138!!!

Nice guy, lousy prof.  Puts way too much calculus on the board.  The course is all formulas as well.  Concerned about the final; we don't even get a cheat sheet (I'll probably still suck!)!  Hate the course itself.. the labs, the material (so boring).

Logan is a very intelligent man, but he is not a good professor because he inadequately explains concepts and theories.  He is quite talented in solving problems; however, his course lacks the theoretical basis of physics and his tests are pure formulas.
dull, cosy, uninteresting.  avoid, esp. for poetry/phys class
HE'S NOT HELPFUL & INSULTING
